approach:
To test our hypothesis, we propose to carry out the following Specific Aims using liver tissue from 6 spaceflight mice, 6 matched ground controls fed the same diet as the spaceflight mice, 6 ground controls fed normal chow and SIRT3-/- and SIRT3 overexpressing ground controls available in the Friedman lab:
1. Measure SIRT3 expression and activity and NAD+ levels;
2. Purify acetylated proteins and identify those with changes in acetylation levels using a targeted mass spectrometry-based proteomics approach;
3. Assess hepatic and mitochondrial function.
